Elba FFA Chapter
August 30 at 7:20 PM ·

Hello FFA Members!

Important Announcement:

To get this year started FFA dues will be $25. If you would like to receive a free John Deere FFA t shirt sponsored by AKRS you must pay $25 by Thursday September 3rd at noon. This t shirt will be provided along with a chapter t shirt. If you do not pay by this deadline you must pay your dues by Wednesday September 9th to receive a chapter t shirt and be an active member. Please note that you must be enrolled in an Agricultural Education class to join FFA too. Looking forward to a great year!

Howard-Greeley County Food Pantry
August 20 at 11:41 AM ·

The Howard Greeley Food Pantry will be distributing fresh fruit, vegetables, dairy and meat today (Thursday, August 20) from 12:30 until 3:00 and again from 4:30-6:00 pm, or until food is gone. If the weather is hot, we will take a 10 min. break during each session. Pull into the lot through the south entrance and stay in your vehicle. Your food will be brought to you. Exit through the north exit. There are no income guidelines for this event. It is open to all. Limit 2 families per vehicle.

Welcome Back Bluejays! We are so excited for the first day of School!
A few things to know for tomorrow.
-Walkers and Drop-offs enter at East Gym Doors (#3)
-Bus Students enter at North doors (#1)
-Parents please do not leave until your student has been checked in and temp taken at the bus stops
-School will be open for student arrivals at 7:30am
-YES there will be breakfast served and lunch
-Masks are NOT required -personal choice

Dismissal will be at 2:00pm
Lets get READY for a Great New Year Bluejays!

post_text:
Supporting Child and Family Wellbeing
We all have a collective responsibility to make sure kids are healthy, safe, and thriving – especially during challenging times. Parents and other caregivers are children’s most important protectors and may need extra support from time to time. We encourage you to check in with caregivers and children you interact with to ask how they’re doing and what they need. Lending an ear and helping families access available supports can go a long way to keeping families well. Thank you for doing your part to support Nebraska’s and our Elba Bluejays children and families! #bluejaystrong #allinthistogether6feetapart #elbapublicschool #selfcareisgoodcare #strongbluejayfamilies

post_text:
Congratulations to the Boy's Basketball players, coaches, cheerleaders, parents and fans. We were awarded the Goldenrod Conference Sportsmanship Award for 2019-20 winter season.
This was the first year we were eligible for the award since bringing back sports 5 years ago. thanks to the players for their effort and respectful play, the coaches for teaching them good sportsmanship and life skills they can use throughout life, their parents for supporting their kids in all they do, and the Elba cheerleaders and fans for showing up and cheering and being positive at games.
Again Congratulations on the Goldenrod Conference Sportsmanship Award for Boy's Basketball.

The Introduction to Agriculture class worked hard on their research projects this year.

Students who submitted their projects on to the State FFA contest were:

Meleyna Kosmicki and Jaime Wysocki with their soil erosion and organic matter experiment.

Bridgette Snyder with her plant growth and lighting experiment that was named a state finalist.

Deanna Fanta with her hamster maze project and she finished 2nd in her category at the state level.

Great job to all of our students! Thank you for all of your hard work!

post_text:
Following guidelines from the Central Health District and the Nebraska Education Commission Elba Public Schools will remain Closed until after May 1, 2020.
An informational letter on educating the students of Elba will be coming to all parents in the next few days via mail. This will outline the plans for educational enrichment activities for the students.
In the meantime please continue at home activities, reading, online activities,free play time and go outside!
Stay Safe, Stay Smart and Stay Healthy. #bluejaystrong #elbapublicschool #togetherwecanjustnotholdinghands

Elba FFA Chapter
December 10, 2019 at 8:28 PM ·

Our FFA Members who competed at District LDE's in Shelton worked hard and did a wonderful job representing Elba. Pictures are below, some of our Junior High Members are not pictured as they had to be back for a basketball game.

Results:

In Agricultural Literacy Speaking Jesse Mills received first purple and will have the opportunity to advance to state, and Klaira Rasmussen received a red ribbon.

In Discovery Speaking both Maycee Radke and Jacob Kosmicki received red ribbons.

In Agricultural Demonstration Jasmine Halsey and Jaden Lambracht received a red ribbon.

In Employment Skills Jordan Seberger received a red ribbon, and Jasmine Halsey received a blue ribbon.

In Creed Speaking Meleyna Kosmicki received the 3rd purple ribbon, and Bridgette Snyder received a red ribbon.

The Conduct of Chapter Meetings Team received a blue ribbon. Team Members were: Bridgette Snyder (Chair), Jaime Wysocki (Vice President), Meleyna Kosmicki (Secretary), Maycee Radke (Reporter), Weston Koperski (Treasurer), Jesse Mills (Advisor), Deanna Fanta (Sentinel).

THURSDAY: COSTUME DAY (Say BOO to Drugs!)

please remember to sign and send back the pledge sheets your children have brought home.
